00:28:25.430 --> 00:28:26.690
smoothly.

00:28:26.690 --> 00:28:28.520
New technologies,
you guys are going

00:28:28.520 --> 00:28:29.870
to develop new technologies.

00:28:29.870 --> 00:28:31.070
That's going to be terrific.

00:28:31.070 --> 00:28:33.060
What's the tsar going
to do about that?

00:28:33.060 --> 00:28:36.590
Well, we'll come back
to some of these issues.

00:28:36.590 --> 00:28:38.630
But governments have
a terrible record

00:28:38.630 --> 00:28:43.040
of pushing the development
of civilian technologies.

00:28:43.040 --> 00:28:45.440
Military technologies,
space technologies,

00:28:45.440 --> 00:28:48.320
where cost doesn't matter, fine.

00:28:48.320 --> 00:28:50.510
Basic research, fine.

00:28:50.510 --> 00:28:55.580
Getting stuff to market at a
reasonable price, bad record.

00:28:55.580 --> 00:28:58.430
So you can't adapt.

00:28:58.430 --> 00:29:02.800
And you can't solve
it with technology.

00:29:02.800 --> 00:29:06.190
You got to reduce emissions.

00:29:06.190 --> 00:29:08.310
Why is reducing emissions hard?

00:29:08.310 --> 00:29:12.160
Oh, well, let me
first fossil fuels.

00:29:12.160 --> 00:29:14.170
Another thing you might
think about doing,

00:29:14.170 --> 00:29:16.630
and you've probably read
about, is geoengineering.

00:29:19.170 --> 00:29:22.140
The simplest way to think about
that is artificial volcanoes.

00:29:22.140 --> 00:29:25.450
You might put sulfate.

00:29:25.450 --> 00:29:29.050
When Mount Pinatubo blew
up, as I understand it,

00:29:29.050 --> 00:29:31.670
there was a discernible cooling.

00:29:31.670 --> 00:29:36.680
Small particles, aerosols in the
stratosphere reflect sunlight.

00:29:36.680 --> 00:29:42.160
So why don't we just either burn
more coal or take the 16-inch

00:29:42.160 --> 00:29:44.230
guns from battleships that
aren't in use anymore,

00:29:44.230 --> 00:29:47.810
turn them up, and fire aerosols
into the stratosphere--

00:29:47.810 --> 00:29:51.830
this is a serious proposal--
to reflect sunlight?

00:29:51.830 --> 00:29:54.950
Well, you might want to have
that in your back pocket

00:29:54.950 --> 00:29:55.730
for emergencies.

00:29:55.730 --> 00:29:59.240
But, first of all, if you have
more CO2 in the atmosphere,

00:29:59.240 --> 00:30:00.650
the ocean becomes more acidic.

00:30:00.650 --> 00:30:02.150
And creatures die.

00:30:02.150 --> 00:30:03.590
Doesn't solve that problem.

00:30:03.590 --> 00:30:05.592
And second, if you
don't reduce emissions,

00:30:05.592 --> 00:30:07.550
you've got to keep doing
more and more of that.

00:30:07.550 --> 00:30:11.540
And that does not sound like
a long-term way forward.

00:30:11.540 --> 00:30:14.930
So CO2 is where
the policy focus is

00:30:14.930 --> 00:30:17.120
because, as we saw from
those earlier graphs,

00:30:17.120 --> 00:30:18.600
it's quite important.

00:30:18.600 --> 00:30:20.840
It lasts a long time.

00:30:20.840 --> 00:30:25.110
We can measure fossil
fuel use pretty easily.

00:30:25.110 --> 00:30:27.110
Think about countries
that import all their oil.

00:30:29.800 --> 00:30:32.830
You can measure
imports pretty easily

00:30:32.830 --> 00:30:35.800
at the ports where they happen.

00:30:35.800 --> 00:30:39.160
You may be wrong, plus or
minus inventory accumulation.

00:30:39.160 --> 00:30:41.110
But it's not easy
to carry and not

00:30:41.110 --> 00:30:45.500
cheap to carry inventories of
crude oil and refined product.

00:30:45.500 --> 00:30:49.270
So in terms of internationally
enforceable agreements,

00:30:49.270 --> 00:30:53.620
fossil fuel is pretty easy
compared to anything else

00:30:53.620 --> 00:30:56.230
you want to think about.

00:30:56.230 --> 00:31:01.000
Another reason you focus on it
is we talked about last week.

00:31:01.000 --> 00:31:05.110
Not only does it
involve durable assets

00:31:05.110 --> 00:31:09.100
that can last a long
time, that are expensive,

00:31:09.100 --> 00:31:12.950
and, thus, expensive
to replace early,

00:31:12.950 --> 00:31:16.170
but there are all these
other path dependencies

00:31:16.170 --> 00:31:18.360
that keep you down a path.

00:31:18.360 --> 00:31:20.610
So that if you want to--
so the energy system

00:31:20.610 --> 00:31:23.640
is a slow ship to turn.

00:31:23.640 --> 00:31:26.580
And if you need to turn
it because its impact last

00:31:26.580 --> 00:31:29.910
100 years and if you
can turn it because you

00:31:29.910 --> 00:31:33.840
can monitor and enforce, that's
a logical place to focus.

00:31:36.590 --> 00:31:38.790
Why is that problem hard?

00:31:38.790 --> 00:31:40.985
Why is it hard to
change emissions?

00:31:40.985 --> 00:31:42.110
Well, we talked about that.

