01:01:20.100 --> 01:01:20.962
And no one else did.

01:01:20.962 --> 01:01:22.920
And it's really not going
to make a difference.

01:01:22.920 --> 01:01:25.020
RICHARD SCHMALENSEE:
Well, there's

01:01:25.020 --> 01:01:29.490
no enforcement mechanism
in the protocol.

01:01:29.490 --> 01:01:31.560
I don't know that the
Framework Convention even

01:01:31.560 --> 01:01:34.140
allows for the possibility
of an enforcement mechanism.

01:01:34.140 --> 01:01:35.370
I'd have to go back and look.

01:01:37.930 --> 01:01:41.320
For simple international
agreements ,

01:01:41.320 --> 01:01:43.330
it hasn't mattered much.

01:01:43.330 --> 01:01:47.890
The Montreal Protocol to phase
out ozone-depleting substances,

01:01:47.890 --> 01:01:51.950
widely ratified not perfect.

01:01:51.950 --> 01:01:55.030
There are some illegal
manufacturing here and there.

01:01:55.030 --> 01:01:58.210
But basically, it's tiny.

01:01:58.210 --> 01:02:01.540
So most governments can
afford to just do it.

01:02:01.540 --> 01:02:03.640
Most countries can
afford to do it.

01:02:03.640 --> 01:02:06.430
It's a rich countries
use those chemicals more

01:02:06.430 --> 01:02:09.430
than poor countries.

01:02:09.430 --> 01:02:11.710
Rich countries can
afford substitutes,

01:02:11.710 --> 01:02:14.740
not perfect, but cheap.

01:02:14.740 --> 01:02:15.580
This, not so cheap.

01:02:15.580 --> 01:02:18.550
And so no enforcement mechanism
there either, as far as I know.

01:02:18.550 --> 01:02:19.870
I don't think there was.

01:02:19.870 --> 01:02:23.740
In any case, it was
never seriously deployed.

01:02:23.740 --> 01:02:27.290
Here, what would you do?

01:02:27.290 --> 01:02:30.740
I mean, the Europeans
are ready to go.

01:02:30.740 --> 01:02:32.000
Everybody was very excited.

01:02:32.000 --> 01:02:33.810
Al Gore flew to Kyoto.

01:02:33.810 --> 01:02:35.900
It was high times.

01:02:35.900 --> 01:02:41.510
And to say the US has always
talked about monitoring.

01:02:41.510 --> 01:02:43.580
No matter who the
president's been,

01:02:43.580 --> 01:02:49.250
we always talk about monitoring
in these kinds of discussions.

01:02:49.250 --> 01:02:51.320
Nobody listens to us much now.

01:02:51.320 --> 01:02:53.270
But we always say,
gee, you ought

01:02:53.270 --> 01:02:59.390
to actually know if somebody
is obeying the agreement.

01:02:59.390 --> 01:03:03.650
That's resisted by
a lot of countries.

01:03:03.650 --> 01:03:04.760
So no.

01:03:04.760 --> 01:03:07.880
And you can now
imagine the beginnings

01:03:07.880 --> 01:03:10.237
of a European reaction.

01:03:10.237 --> 01:03:10.820
Wait a minute.

01:03:10.820 --> 01:03:12.710
We're doing all this?

01:03:12.710 --> 01:03:15.380
And what are all these
other people doing?

01:03:15.380 --> 01:03:16.580
They're smiling at us.

01:03:19.280 --> 01:03:22.310
It raises the cost of
our heavy industry,

01:03:22.310 --> 01:03:24.500
our energy-intensive industry.

01:03:24.500 --> 01:03:26.450
And wait a minute.

01:03:26.450 --> 01:03:28.400
Why are we doing this again?

