01:05:00.920 --> 01:05:02.510
at least monitor.

01:05:02.510 --> 01:05:04.050
You may not be able to enforce.

01:05:04.050 --> 01:05:07.460
So I can't see us signing
something, ratifying

01:05:07.460 --> 01:05:11.720
something that doesn't have at
least monitoring provisions.

01:05:11.720 --> 01:05:19.290
Enforcement, look at attempts
to take action against Syria.

01:05:19.290 --> 01:05:23.000
The world community doesn't
lightly enforce stuff.

01:05:23.000 --> 01:05:27.390
But every so often, Syria,
Iran, something gets done.

01:05:27.390 --> 01:05:28.578
But doesn't get done easily.

01:05:28.578 --> 01:05:29.870
Doesn't get done automatically.

01:05:29.870 --> 01:05:31.130
It's a big political deal.

01:05:31.130 --> 01:05:31.820
David?

01:05:31.820 --> 01:05:35.310
AUDIENCE: How is this not led
to a stronger partnership laws?

01:05:35.310 --> 01:05:40.400
In that, I see it as a place
where a more developed nation

01:05:40.400 --> 01:05:42.770
that has high technology
institutions like MIT

01:05:42.770 --> 01:05:46.160
could come in and talk
to a place like that.

01:05:46.160 --> 01:05:49.115
There's already a fair amount
of infrastructure investment

01:05:49.115 --> 01:05:49.880
that's made.

01:05:49.880 --> 01:05:52.610
And a lot of it can be in the
terms of low-interest loans

01:05:52.610 --> 01:05:56.720
or provide experts to help
build up the infrastructure

01:05:56.720 --> 01:05:58.380
because your cost is lower.

01:05:58.380 --> 01:06:00.020
And you're developing
something new.

01:06:00.020 --> 01:06:03.560
And you're fostering global
investment here in the States

01:06:03.560 --> 01:06:05.180
by making that part of your--

01:06:05.180 --> 01:06:05.870
RICHARD SCHMALENSEE: Available.

01:06:05.870 --> 01:06:06.500
AUDIENCE: --value add.

01:06:06.500 --> 01:06:07.595
You're also helping
internationally.

01:06:07.595 --> 01:06:08.678
How is that not happening?

01:06:08.678 --> 01:06:11.060
RICHARD SCHMALENSEE: Well,
it happens to some extent.

01:06:11.060 --> 01:06:15.170
There's a problem of
measurement, right?

01:06:15.170 --> 01:06:20.680
The European system--
the Kyoto Protocol

01:06:20.680 --> 01:06:27.220
provides for joint
implementation.

01:06:27.220 --> 01:06:29.330
Well, I forget the
exact language.

01:06:29.330 --> 01:06:29.830
Hmm?

01:06:29.830 --> 01:06:32.740
The Clean Development
Mechanism, CDM.

01:06:32.740 --> 01:06:36.700
If you're a European
company, you

01:06:36.700 --> 01:06:40.240
can meet some of
your obligations

01:06:40.240 --> 01:06:44.450
by reducing emissions
in a poor country.

01:06:44.450 --> 01:06:51.230
So you can go to China and do a
deal, bring in new technology,

01:06:51.230 --> 01:06:54.890
do something that
will reduce emissions.

01:06:54.890 --> 01:06:56.140
And that will give you credit.

01:06:56.140 --> 01:06:59.950
And that's exactly
that kind of thinking.

01:06:59.950 --> 01:07:02.770
Even though China
isn't participating,

01:07:02.770 --> 01:07:05.300
it's still cheaper to
do reductions there.

01:07:05.300 --> 01:07:09.310
So let's find a way to give
countries in Europe credit

01:07:09.310 --> 01:07:11.888
for reductions in China.

01:07:11.888 --> 01:07:13.180
There are a couple of problems.

01:07:16.840 --> 01:07:19.500
Well, it all boils
down to one problem

01:07:19.500 --> 01:07:22.920
really, which is, how
do you measure it?

01:07:22.920 --> 01:07:27.270
Because you're reducing
over what would have been.

01:07:27.270 --> 01:07:29.850
So you modernize a factory.

01:07:29.850 --> 01:07:32.040
So would that factory
have been running forever

01:07:32.040 --> 01:07:33.360
with old technology?

01:07:33.360 --> 01:07:34.920
Or would it have been torn down?

01:07:34.920 --> 01:07:37.500
Or would it have been
modernized anyway?

01:07:37.500 --> 01:07:43.390
So either you're real
light on how you do this,

01:07:43.390 --> 01:07:46.690
and you don't impose
real tough restrictions

01:07:46.690 --> 01:07:49.210
and then you're not
getting real reductions.

01:07:49.210 --> 01:07:51.880
Or you make it really
hard to document.

01:07:51.880 --> 01:07:53.770
In which case, you
kill the market.

01:07:53.770 --> 01:07:55.180
So it happens.

01:07:55.180 --> 01:07:56.560
And it happens to some extent.

01:07:56.560 --> 01:07:58.518
The Europeans have gotten
a little tired of it,

01:07:58.518 --> 01:08:01.850
as I recall, thinking that
it's been a little too easy.

01:08:01.850 --> 01:08:08.960
But one of the features of the
Waxman-Markey bill in the US,

01:08:08.960 --> 01:08:12.200
which was the cap and trade
bill-- it was killed--

01:08:12.200 --> 01:08:13.385
it allowed for that.

01:08:16.529 --> 01:08:18.990
It covered only fossil fuels.

01:08:18.990 --> 01:08:22.470
But it allowed
companies to get credit

01:08:22.470 --> 01:08:26.100
for things done in agriculture.

01:08:26.100 --> 01:08:28.490
So you could change land use.

01:08:28.490 --> 01:08:33.710
And it was a giveaway
to agriculture

01:08:33.710 --> 01:08:36.680
basically because the standards
were going to be pretty easy.

01:08:36.680 --> 01:08:39.229
But it was that
same notion that I

01:08:39.229 --> 01:08:42.920
want to reach out beyond
places that I can price

01:08:42.920 --> 01:08:45.620
to give people incentives.

01:08:45.620 --> 01:08:49.399
But it's really hard because
you can measure what is emitted.

01:08:49.399 --> 01:08:54.020
You can never measure
what would have been.

01:08:54.020 --> 01:08:56.840
You could see the same
problem with forests

01:08:56.840 --> 01:08:58.700
if you think for just a minute.

01:08:58.700 --> 01:09:00.663
If I pay you not to
cut down a forest,

01:09:00.663 --> 01:09:02.330
does that mean the
guy across the street

01:09:02.330 --> 01:09:07.310
cuts his down to provide
the timber or what?

01:09:07.310 --> 01:09:11.300
And you would never have cut
it down or you would have?

01:09:11.300 --> 01:09:15.109
So it's a natural model.

01:09:15.109 --> 01:09:19.880
If there were a common regime,
a cap and trade or a tax regime,

01:09:19.880 --> 01:09:22.520
that would happen
automatically, easily.

01:09:22.520 --> 01:09:24.529
And you wouldn't have
a measurement problem.

01:09:24.529 --> 01:09:27.109
It's just hard to do it
without such a thing.

01:09:27.109 --> 01:09:30.319
US companies, there's some
sort of informal trading

01:09:30.319 --> 01:09:31.550
in carbon credits in the.

01:09:31.550 --> 01:09:35.479
US and companies will
do stuff like this

01:09:35.479 --> 01:09:37.340
and take credit for it.

01:09:37.340 --> 01:09:38.899
Perfectly fine activities.

01:09:38.899 --> 01:09:42.326
It's socially
responsible and all that.

01:09:42.326 --> 01:09:43.534
But it's just hard to assess.

01:09:43.534 --> 01:09:46.531
AUDIENCE: Where's the
